      "content": "I understand you’re in a pinch, but honey, while it does have some antibacterial properties, is not a substitute for professional medical care, especially for a deep cut. The wound could be a sign of infection or might need stitches. I would advise you to seek medical attention immediately. In the meantime, keep the wound clean and apply gentle pressure with a clean cloth. Avoid using honey or any other home remedy as it could worsen the situation. Stay safe!",
