      "content": "Honey, even medical grade, is not a replacement for professional medical care. A slow ooze can be a sign of an infection or a complication that requires a medical professional's attention. The risks of not seeking proper care can include worsening of the wound, potential infection, and other complications. It's always best to err on the side of caution with health matters. If it's an emergency, even though it's inconvenient, the cost of the clinic and the drive are minor compared to the risk of a serious infection or other complications. It's better to be safe than sorry. If you really must wait until morning, keep the wound clean and covered with a sterile bandage, and monitor it closely for any signs of worsening. But seriously, please consider going to the clinic. Your health is irreplaceable.",
